==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: euphroe
<hw>eu"phroe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol.
uncertain.]</ety> <def>A block or long slat of wood, perforated for the
passage of the crowfoot, or cords by which an awning is held up.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>uphroe</asp> and <asp>uvrou</asp>.]</altsp>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>euphuism</ent>⟦br⟧
